      <hedline>
        <hl1>NEW ROCHELLE: NEW SCANNER</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By ROBERT WORTH</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Worth, Robert</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Sound Shore Medical Center in New Rochelle, NY, acquries new variety of CT scanner, which provides images up to six times faster than traditional ones (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Sound Shore Medical Center in New Rochelle has acquired a new variety of CT (CAT) scanner, the first in the county, which provides images up to six times faster than traditional CT scans. Because the new scanner works fast, it tends to reduce the anxieties patients often feel during CT scans. The device, known as the LightSpeed scanner, costs more than $1 million, a hospital spokesman said.</p>
        <p>ROBERT WORTH</p>
      </block>
